---
/**
 * Disclaimer Page
 * Legal disclaimer for Qurbani Foundation
 */
export const prerender = false;

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = "February 23, 2026";
---

<Layout title="Disclaimer | Qurbani Foundation">
  <Navbar />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#255764] to-[#1a4a55] pt-32 pb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
          Disclaimer
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
          Last Updated: {lastUpdated}
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">

          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-[#D97706] p-6 mb-8 rounded-r-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-700 m-0">
              Please read this disclaimer carefully before using the Qurbani Foundation website or making any donations.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">1. General Information</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            The information provided on this website is for general informational purposes only. Qurbani Foundation makes every effort to ensure the accuracy of the information presented, but we make no warranties or representations regarding its completeness, accuracy, reliability, or suitability for any particular purpose.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">2. Nonprofit Status</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Qurbani Foundation is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization (EIN: 38-4109146) based in Teaneck, New Jersey, United States. Donations to Qurbani Foundation are tax-deductible to the extent allowed by law. However, we recommend consulting with a qualified tax professional regarding your specific tax situation.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">3. Religious and Islamic Guidance</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            While Qurbani Foundation provides information about Islamic charitable obligations such as Zakat, Zakat ul-Fitr, Fidya, Kaffarah, and Qurbani, this information is for educational purposes only and should not be considered as religious rulings (fatwas). We encourage donors to consult with qualified Islamic scholars regarding their specific religious obligations and questions.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">4. Zakat Eligibility</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Our designation of certain programs as "Zakat-eligible" is based on our understanding of Islamic jurisprudence and the categories of Zakat recipients outlined in the Quran. However, the ultimate responsibility for ensuring your Zakat is properly allocated rests with the individual donor. We recommend consulting with a knowledgeable scholar if you have questions about Zakat eligibility.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">5. Program Implementation</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            While we strive to implement all programs as described on our website:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Programs may be modified based on field conditions, local regulations, or unforeseen circumstances</li>
            <li>Images and descriptions represent typical program activities but may vary by location</li>
            <li>Beneficiary stories are shared with consent and may be anonymized for protection</li>
            <li>Project timelines may be adjusted due to factors beyond our control</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">6. Fund Allocation</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Qurbani Foundation maintains a 100% Zakat policy, meaning all Zakat funds go directly to eligible recipients. For other donations, while we make every effort to honor donor intent and allocate funds to specified programs, we reserve the right to redirect donations to similar programs or areas of greatest need if the designated program is fully funded, no longer active, or cannot be implemented as planned.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">7. Donation Processing</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Qurbani Foundation accepts donations through various methods including credit cards, debit cards, and other electronic payment methods. Please note:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>One-time donations are processed immediately upon submission</li>
            <li>Recurring monthly donations are charged on the same date each month</li>
            <li>All transactions are processed securely through our payment partners</li>
            <li>Tax receipts are issued for all eligible donations</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">8. Recurring Donations</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            For recurring (monthly) donations:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>You may cancel, increase, or decrease your recurring donation at any time</li>
            <li>Please provide at least 5 business days notice before your next scheduled payment to make changes</li>
            <li>To modify or cancel your recurring donation, contact us at <a href="mailto:donorcare@qurbani.com" class="text-[#D97706] hover:underline">donorcare@qurbani.com</a> or call +1 (800) 900 0027</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">9. Refund Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            We understand that circumstances may change. Qurbani Foundation will consider refund requests under the following guidelines:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Refund requests made within 30 days of donation may be honored, provided funds have not been disbursed</li>
            <li>Credit card donations will be refunded to the original card used</li>
            <li>For time-sensitive donations (Qurbani, Ramadan, emergency relief), refunds may not be possible once distribution has begun</li>
            <li>If a tax receipt was issued, an amended receipt will be provided upon refund</li>
            <li>To request a refund, please email <a href="mailto:donorcare@qurbani.com" class="text-[#D97706] hover:underline">donorcare@qurbani.com</a> with your donation details</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">10. Third-Party Links</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Our website may contain links to third-party websites. These links are provided for your convenience and informational purposes only. Qurbani Foundation does not endorse, control, or assume responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites. We encourage you to review the terms and policies of any external sites you visit.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">11. No Professional Advice</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Nothing on this website constitutes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Legal advice</li>
            <li>Tax advice</li>
            <li>Financial advice</li>
            <li>Religious rulings (fatwas)</li>
            <li>Medical advice</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            For matters requiring professional expertise, please consult with appropriately qualified professionals.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, Qurbani Foundation, its officers, directors, employees, volunteers, and agents shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of this website, reliance on any information provided, or any donations made through this platform.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">13. Accuracy of Information</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            While we strive to keep the information on our website accurate and up-to-date, we make no representations or warranties of any kind, express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability, suitability, or availability of the website or the information, products, services, or related graphics contained on the website.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">14. Testimonials and Impact Stories</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            Testimonials and impact stories shared on our website represent individual experiences and may not reflect typical results. Names and identifying details may be changed to protect the privacy of beneficiaries. Photos may be representative of our work rather than specific individuals mentioned.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">15. Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
            We reserve the right to modify this disclaimer at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to this page. Your continued use of our website following any changes constitutes acceptance of those changes.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#255764] mt-10 mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">16. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            If you have questions about this disclaimer, please contact us:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2"><strong>Qurbani Foundation</strong></p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-1">145 Sherwood Ave</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-1">Teaneck, NJ 07666</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-1">Email: <a href="mailto:donorcare@qurbani.com" class="text-[#D97706] hover:underline">donorcare@qurbani.com</a></p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Phone: +1 (800) 900 0027</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
